<title>Domains and constraints in the OASIS specification</title>
<shortdesc>OASIS distributes grammar files for a set of domains and constraints. </shortdesc>
<refbody>
<section id="section-1">
<p>A designation of (map) after the domain name indicates that the domain only specializes map
    elements; a designation of (topic) indicates that the domain specializes elements that are only
    available in topic or that it <ph >can</ph> only be used in topics. A
    designation of (map/topic) indicates that the domain specializes elements that are common to
    both maps and topics, so could be used in either even if it is generally intended for one or the
    other. Attribute domains <ph >can</ph> always be used in both topics and
    maps.</p>
</section>
